<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-23T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="120" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.7962/2: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chairman of the American
                                    Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-23T10:00:00-05:00">December 23, 1933—10
                                        a.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>117. Department’s 101, December 19, 7 p.m. The President hopes that
                                progress can be made with respect to fast air communication and
                                establishment beacons and guides before adjournment of conference.
                                He suggests that a conference of experts of the interested countries
                                to be held in Washington might be helpful.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>